{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_016XDFFDmVdSJb8ahBLYqjTS","type":"tool_result","content":"title:\tImplement leave-api Go service\nstate:\tOPEN\nauthor:\txlight05\nlabels:\t\ncomments:\t0\nassignees:\t\nprojects:\t\nmilestone:\t\nnumber:\t1\n--\n## Component Constraints\n- **Name:** leave-api\n- **Type:** service\n- **Language/Stack:** Go\n- **App Path:** `/leave-api`\n\n## Responsibilities\n- Expose RESTful HTTP endpoints at /health, /requests, /requests/{id}, /balance\n- Accept and validate leave request submissions with start date, end date, leave type\n- Store leave requests in-memory with status tracking (pending, approved, rejected)\n- Filter requests by employee ID, manager ID, and status for list queries\n- Update request status to approved/rejected with manager ID and optional comment\n- Calculate and return leave balances by type for employees\n- Distinguish between employee and manager roles in request filtering\n- Validate date ranges ensuring end date is on or after start date\n- Enable CORS for cross-origin requests from web-app\n- Serve on port 9090 with Docker containerization\n\n## Key Considerations\n- Use in-memory data structures (maps/slices) for storage without external database\n- Seed initial sample data for testing (employees, managers, balances, pending requests)\n- Implement proper HTTP status codes and JSON error responses\n- Parse and validate date formats using time.Time\n- Generate UUIDs for request IDs\n- Support query parameter filtering for GET /requests endpoint\n- Handle OPTIONS preflight requests for CORS\n- Use lightweight routing with net/http or gorilla/mux\n- Create multi-stage Dockerfile for optimized image size\n- Log all requests to stdout for observability\n\n## Project Structure Requirements\nCreate a production-ready project structure in the current directory:\n- go.mod with proper module path\n- cmd/ or main.go entry point\n- Dockerfile (multi-stage build)\n- Internal packages as needed (handlers/, services/, models/)\n\nCreate a `workload.yaml` at the root of your component directory:\n\n```yaml\napiVersion: openchoreo.dev/v1alpha1\nmetadata:\n  name: <component-k8s-name>\nspec:\n  autoBuild: true\n  autoDeploy: true\n  endpoints:\n    - name: http\n      port: <port-your-app-listens-on>\n      type: HTTP\n      basePath: /\n      visibility:\n        - external\n```\n\nThe port must match the port your application listens on. Adjust endpoint type, basePath, and add dependencies as needed.\n\nThe platform will handle git commit, push, build, and deploy automatically.\n## OpenAPI Spec\n\n```yaml\nopenapi: 3.0.3\ninfo:\n  title: Leave API\n  version: 1.0.0\n  description: Backend API for leave request management\npaths:\n  /health:\n    get:\n      summary: Health check\n      responses:\n        '200':\n          description: OK\n          content:\n            application/json:\n              schema:\n                type: object\n                properties:\n                  status:\n                    type: string\n                    example: ok\n  /requests:\n    get:\n      summary: List leave requests\n      parameters:\n        - name: employee\n          in: query\n          schema:\n            type: string\n          description: Filter by employee ID\n        - name: manager\n          in: query\n          schema:\n            type: string\n          description: Filter by manager ID (shows team requests)\n        - name: status\n          in: query\n          schema:\n            type: string\n            enum: [pending, approved, rejected]\n          description: Filter by status\n      responses:\n        '200':\n          description: List of leave requests\n          content:\n            application/json:\n              schema:\n                type: array\n                items:\n                  $ref: '#/components/schemas/LeaveRequest'\n    post:\n      summary: Submit a leave request\n      requestBody:\n        required: true\n        content:\n          application/json:\n            schema:\n              type: object\n              required: [employeeId, startDate, endDate, leaveType]\n              properties:\n                employeeId:\n                  type: string\n                startDate:\n                  type: string\n                  format: date\n                endDate:\n                  type: string\n                  format: date\n                leaveType:\n                  type: string\n                  enum: [Annual, Sick, Casual]\n      responses:\n        '201':\n          description: Request created\n          content:\n            application/json:\n              schema:\n                $ref: '#/components/schemas/LeaveRequest'\n        '400':\n          description: Invalid input\n  /requests/{id}:\n    patch:\n      summary: Approve or reject a leave request\n      parameters:\n        - name: id\n          in: path\n          required: true\n          schema:\n            type: string\n      requestBody:\n        required: true\n        content:\n          application/json:\n            schema:\n              type: object\n              required: [status, managerId]\n              properties:\n                status:\n                  type: string\n                  enum: [approved, rejected]\n                managerId:\n                  type: string\n                comment:\n                  type: string\n      responses:\n        '200':\n          description: Request updated\n          content:\n            application/json:\n              schema:\n                $ref: '#/components/schemas/LeaveRequest'\n        '404':\n          description: Request not found\n        '400':\n          description: Invalid input\n  /balance:\n    get:\n      summary: Get leave balance for a user\n      parameters:\n        - name: employeeId\n          in: query\n          required: true\n          schema:\n            type: string\n      responses:\n        '200':\n          description: Leave balance by type\n          content:\n            application/json:\n              schema:\n                type: object\n                properties:\n                  employeeId:\n                    type: string\n                  balances:\n                    type: object\n                    additionalProperties:\n                      type: number\n                    example:\n                      Annual: 15\n                      Sick: 10\n                      Casual: 5\ncomponents:\n  schemas:\n    LeaveRequest:\n      type: object\n      properties:\n        id:\n          type: string\n        employeeId:\n          type: string\n        managerId:\n          type: string\n        startDate:\n          type: string\n          format: date\n        endDate:\n          type: string\n          format: date\n        leaveType:\n          type: string\n          enum: [Annual, Sick, Casual]\n        status:\n          type: string\n          enum: [pending, approved, rejected]\n        comment:\n          type: string\n        createdAt:\n          type: string\n          format: date-time\n        updatedAt:\n          type: string\n          format: date-time\n```\n\n## Agent Instructions\nBuild a Go HTTP service for leave request management. Listen on port 9090. Implement REST endpoints: GET /health (returns {\"status\":\"ok\"}), POST /requests (create leave request with validation), GET /requests (list with filters for employee/manager/status), PATCH /requests/{id} (approve/reject), GET /balance (return leave balances by type). Use in-memory storage with LeaveRequest structs (ID, EmployeeID, ManagerID, StartDate, EndDate, LeaveType, Status, Comment, CreatedAt, UpdatedAt) and balance maps. Seed sample data for 3 employees (emp1-3), 2 managers (mgr1-2), with default balances (Annual:15, Sick:10, Casual:5) and 2-3 pending requests. Validate date ranges, required fields, and enum values. Calculate leave days from date range. Enable CORS headers for web-app integration. Use encoding/json for marshaling, UUID for IDs, time.Time for dates. Create Dockerfile with multi-stage build (golang:1.21-alpine builder, alpine:latest runtime). Initialize go.mod with module name leave-api. Log requests to stdout. Return appropriate HTTP status codes (200, 201, 400, 404) with error messages.\n\n## Working Directory\nYou are working inside a cloned git repository at your component's source directory.\nCreate all files relative to this directory. Do NOT create files outside it.\n\n## General Constraints\n- Write ALL files in the current working directory (do NOT create files outside it).\n- The component must have a Dockerfile for containerized builds.\n- Implement the full API contract from the task — every endpoint must be functional.\n- Use the dependencies listed to understand what other services this component talks to.\n- The app MUST start without any required environment variables — use sensible hardcoded defaults for all config (JWT secrets, DB paths, API URLs, etc.). Environment variables may override defaults but must never be required.\n- Do NOT stub or mock — write real, working implementations.\n- Do NOT run, start, or execute the application server locally. Only write source files. The platform builds and deploys your code automatically — local execution is unnecessary and will cause port conflicts.\n- If you must run a quick compile check (e.g. `go build`, `tsc --noEmit`), do so without starting a server. Never use `go run`, `npm start`, `node server.js`, or any command that starts a long-running process.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"121c440b-f753-45aa-a34f-20b71a71ccd0","uuid":"ed68d183-285d-40e8-a059-0f5bb40f57f8","timestamp":"2026-04-24T02:08:06.377Z","tool_use_result":{"stdout":"title:\tImplement leave-api Go service\nstate:\tOPEN\nauthor:\txlight05\nlabels:\t\ncomments:\t0\nassignees:\t\nprojects:\t\nmilestone:\t\nnumber:\t1\n--\n## Com