{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01Y8vgRZh7oK6NiZKR65k51p","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01WCHdSKc7ZxhBip9Hd73UwA","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"cat /Users/wso2/.asdlc/repos/default/mmm/.asdlc/design.json | python3 -m json.tool 2>/dev/null | head -100","description":"Check design.json for task IDs"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":351,"cache_read_input_tokens":22102,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":351,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":58,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"global"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"121c440b-f753-45aa-a34f-20b71a71ccd0","uuid":"2cfd3bc0-2a91-4d90-914e-23b6b3cbc8df"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01WCHdSKc7ZxhBip9Hd73UwA","type":"tool_result","content":"{\n    \"overview\": \"A leave management system with a React frontend (web-app) that calls a Go backend API (service) for leave request operations. The backend exposes RESTful endpoints for submitting, approving, and querying leave requests, plus checking balances. Communication is synchronous HTTP/JSON between the web-app and the API.\",\n    \"requirements\": [\n        \"Employees must be able to submit leave requests specifying start date, end date, and leave type\",\n        \"Managers must be able to view pending leave requests from their direct reports\",\n        \"Managers must be able to approve or reject leave requests with optional comments\",\n        \"Employees must be able to view the status of their own leave requests\",\n        \"All users must be able to check their remaining leave balance by leave type\",\n        \"The system must distinguish between employee and manager roles\",\n        \"Leave requests must track status: pending, approved, or rejected\",\n        \"The system must calculate leave days from start and end dates\",\n        \"All components must expose a /health endpoint for readiness checks\"\n    ],\n    \"components\": [\n        {\n            \"name\": \"leave-web\",\n            \"componentType\": \"web-app\",\n            \"language\": \"TypeScript / React\",\n            \"dependsOn\": [\n                \"leave-api\"\n            ],\n            \"entrypoint\": \"deployment/web-application\",\n            \"buildpack\": \"docker\",\n            \"appPath\": \"/leave-web\",\n            \"openAPISpec\": \"openapi: 3.0.3\\ninfo:\\n  title: Leave Web Application\\n  version: 1.0.0\\n  description: Frontend SPA for leave management\\npaths:\\n  /health:\\n    get:\\n      summary: Health check\\n      responses:\\n        '200':\\n          description: OK\\n          content:\\n            application/json:\\n              schema:\\n                type: object\\n                properties:\\n                  status:\\n                    type: string\\n                    example: ok\",\n            \"componentAgentInstructions\": \"Build a React single-page application in TypeScript. Use Create React App or Vite. Serve on port 3000. Implement a health endpoint at GET /health returning {\\\"status\\\":\\\"ok\\\"}. Create pages: (1) Leave Request Form \\u2014 date pickers for start/end dates, dropdown for leave type (Annual, Sick, Casual), submit button calling POST /leave-api/requests. (2) My Requests \\u2014 table showing user's requests with columns: dates, type, status, manager comment. Fetch from GET /leave-api/requests?employee={userId}. (3) Manager Dashboard \\u2014 table of pending requests from team with Approve/Reject buttons calling PATCH /leave-api/requests/{id}. Fetch from GET /leave-api/requests?status=pending&manager={userId}. (4) Leave Balance \\u2014 display remaining days per leave type from GET /leave-api/balance. Use React Router for navigation. Mock user authentication by storing userId and role (employee/manager) in sessionStorage. Show/hide Manager Dashboard based on role. Use fetch or axios for API calls to leave-api service. Handle errors with user-friendly messages. Use basic styling with CSS or a UI library like Material-UI. Dockerfile: multi-stage build with Node 18, npm install, npm run build, serve with nginx:alpine copying build to /usr/share/nginx/html. Expose port 3000 via nginx config.\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"name\": \"leave-api\",\n            \"componentType\": \"service\",\n            \"language\": \"Go\",\n            \"dependsOn\": [],\n            \"entrypoint\": \"deployment/service\",\n            \"buildpack\": \"docker\",\n            \"appPath\": \"/leave-api\",\n            \"openAPISpec\": \"openapi: 3.0.3\\ninfo:\\n  title: Leave API\\n  version: 1.0.0\\n  description: Backend API for leave request management\\npaths:\\n  /health:\\n    get:\\n      summary: Health check\\n      responses:\\n        '200':\\n          description: OK\\n          content:\\n            application/json:\\n              schema:\\n                type: object\\n                properties:\\n                  status:\\n                    type: string\\n                    example: ok\\n  /requests:\\n    get:\\n      summary: List leave requests\\n      parameters:\\n        - name: employee\\n          in: query\\n          schema:\\n            type: string\\n          description: Filter by employee ID\\n        - name: manager\\n          in: query\\n          schema:\\n            type: string\\n          description: Filter by manager ID (shows team requests)\\n        - name: status\\n          in: query\\n          schema:\\n            type: string\\n            enum: [pending, approved, rejected]\\n          description: Filter by status\\n      responses:\\n        '200':\\n          description: List of leave requests\\n          content:\\n            application/json:\\n              schema:\\n                type: array\\n                items:\\n                  $ref: '#/components/schemas/LeaveRequest'\\n    post:\\n      summary: Submit a leave request\\n      requestBody:\\n        required: true\\n        content:\\n          application/json:\\n            schema:\\n              type: object\\n              required: [employeeId, startDate, endDate, leaveType]\\n              properties:\\n                employeeId:\\n                  type: string\\n                startDate:\\n                  type: string\\n                  format: date\\n                endDate:\\n                  type: string\\n                  format: date\\n                leaveType:\\n                  type: string\\n                  enum: [Annual, Sick, Casual]\\n      responses:\\n        '201':\\n          description: Request created\\n          content:\\n            application/json:\\n              schema:\\n                $ref: '#/components/schemas/LeaveRequest'\\n        '400':\\n          description: Invalid input\\n  /requests/{id}:\\n    patch:\\n      summary: Approve or reject a leave request\\n      parameters:\\n        - name: id\\n          in: path\\n          required: true\\n          schema:\\n            type: string\\n      requestBody:\\n        required: true\\n        content:\\n          application/json:\\n            schema:\\n              type: object\\n              required: [status, managerId]\\n              properties:\\n                status:\\n                  type: string\\n                  enum: [approved, rejected]\\n                managerId:\\n                  type: string\\n                comment:\\n                  type: string\\n      responses:\\n        '200':\\n          description: Request updated\\n          content:\\n            application/json:\\n              schema:\\n                $ref: '#/components/schemas/LeaveRequest'\\n        '404':\\n          description: Request not found\\n        '400':\\n          description: Invalid input\\n  /balance:\\n    get:\\n      summary: Get leave balance for a user\\n      parameters:\\n        - name: employeeId\\n          in: query\\n          required: true\\n          schema:\\n            type: string\\n      responses:\\n        '200':\\n          description: Leave balance by type\\n          content:\\n            application/json:\\n              schema:\\n                type: object\\n                properties:\\n                  employeeId:\\n                    type: string\\n                  balances:\\n                    type: object\\n                    additionalProperties:\\n                      type: number\\n                    example:\\n                      Annual: 15\\n                      Sick: 10\\n                      Casual: 5\\ncomponents:\\n  schemas:\\n    LeaveRequest:\\n      type: object\\n      properties:\\n        id:\\n          type: string\\n        employeeId:\\n          type: string\\n        managerId:\\n          type: string\\n        startDate:\\n          type: string\\n          format: date\\n        endDate:\\n          type: string\\n          format: date\\n        leaveType:\\n          type: string\\n          enum: [Annual, Sick, Casual]\\n        status:\\n          type: string\\n          enum: [pending, approved, rejected]\\n        comment:\\n          type: string\\n        createdAt:\\n          type: string\\n          format: date-time\\n        updatedAt:\\n          type: string\\n          format: date-time\",\n            \"componentAgentInstructions\": \"Build a Go HTTP service using net/http. Listen on port 9090. Implement GET /health returning JSON {\\\"status\\\":\\\"ok\\\"}. Use in-memory data structures (maps, slices) for storage: a slice of LeaveRequest structs and a map of employee balances. LeaveRequest struct: ID (string, UUID), EmployeeID (string), ManagerID (string), StartDate (time.Time), EndDate (time.Time), LeaveType (string: Annual/Sick/Casual), Status (string: pending/approved/rejected), Comment (string), CreatedAt (time.Time), UpdatedAt (time.Time). Initialize with sample data: 3 employees with IDs emp1, emp2, emp3; manager IDs mgr1, mgr2; balances map with Annual:15, Sick:10, Casual:5 per employee. Seed 2-3 pending requests. POST /requests: parse JSON body, validate required fields and date range (endDate >= startDate), generate UUID, set status=pending, store, return 201 with created object. GET /requests: support query params employee, manager, status; filter in-memory slice; manager filter returns requests where request.ManagerID equals query param; return filtered array. PATCH /requests/{id}: find by ID, validate status is approved or rejected, update Status, ManagerID, Comment, UpdatedAt; return 200 with updated object or 404 if not found. GET /balance?employeeId=X: return JSON object with employeeId and balances map. Use encoding/json for marshaling. Enable CORS headers (Access-Control-Allow-Origin: *, Access-Control-Allow-Methods: GET,POST,PATCH,OPTIONS, Access-Control-Allow-Headers: Content-Type). Handle OPTIONS preflight. Use http.HandleFunc for routing or a lightweight router like gorilla/mux. Log requests to stdout. Dockerfile: FROM golang:1.21-alpine AS builder, WORKDIR /app, COPY go.mod go.sum ./, RUN go mod download, COPY . ., RUN go build -o leave-api .; FROM alpine:latest, COPY --from=builder /app/leave-api /leave-api, EXPOSE 9090, CMD [\\\"/leave-api\\\"]. Ensure go.mod module name is leave-api. Use time.Parse for date parsing. Return appropriate HTTP status codes and error messages for validation failures.\"\n        }\n    ],\n    \"sourceSpec\": \"spec-v1\"\n}","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"121c440b-f753-45aa-a34f-20b71a71ccd0","uuid":"f8ce01c3-8a94-48c9-b314-1f9740ddaef9","timestamp":"2026-04-24T02:09:17.677Z","tool_use_result":{"stdout":"{\n    \"overview\": \"A leave management system with a React frontend (web-app) that calls a Go backend API (service) for leave request operations. The backend exposes RESTful endpoints for submitting, approving, and querying leave requests, plus checking balances. Communication is synchronous HTTP/JSON between the web-app and the API.\",\n    \"requirements\": [\n        \"Employees must be able to submit leave requests specifying start date, end date, and leave type\",\n        \"Managers must be able to view pending leave requests from their direct reports\",\n        \"Managers must be able to approve or reject leave requests with optional comments\",\n        \"Employees must be able to view the status of their own leave requests\",\n        \"All users must be able to check their remaining leave balance by leave type\",\n        \"The system must distinguish between employee and manager roles\",\n        \"Leave requests must track status: pending, approved, or rejected\",\n        \"The system must calculate leave days from start and end dates\",\n        \"All components must expose a /health endpoint for readiness checks\"\n    ],\n    \"components\": [\n        {\n            \"name\": \"leave-web\",\n            \"componentType\": \"web-app\",\n            \"language\": \"TypeScript / React\",\n            \"dependsOn\": [\n                \"leave-api\"\n            ],\n            \"entrypoint\": \"deployment/web-application\",\n            \"buildpack\": \"docker\",\n            \"appPath\": \"/leave-web\",\n            \"openAPISpec\": \"openapi: 3.0.3\\ninfo:\\n  title: Leave Web Application\\n  version: 1.0.0\\n  description: Frontend SPA for leave management\\npaths:\\n  /health:\\n    get:\\n      summary: Health check\\n      responses:\\n        '200':\\n          description: OK\\n          content:\\n            application/json:\\n              schema:\\n                type: object\\n                properties:\\n                  status:\\n                    type: string\\n                    example: ok\",\n            \"componentAgentInstructions\": \"Build a React single-page application in TypeScript. Use Create React App or Vite. Serve on port 3000. Implement a health endpoint at GET /health returning {\\\"status\\\":\\\"ok\\\"}. Create pages: (1) Leave Request Form \\u2014 date pickers for start/end dates, dropdown for leave type (Annual, Sick, Casual), submit button calling POST /leave-api/requests. (2) My Requests \\u2014 table showing user's requests with columns: dates, type, status, manager comment. Fetch from GET /leave-api/requests?employee={userId}. (3) Manager Dashboard \\u2014 table of pending requests from team with Approve/Reject buttons calling PATCH /leave-api/requests/{id}. Fetch from GET /leave-api/requests?status=pending&manager={userId}. (4) Leave Balance \\u2014 display remaining days per leave type from GET /leave-api/balance. Use React Router for navigation. Mock user authentication by storing userId and role (employee/manager) in sessionStorage. Show/hide Manager Dashboard based on role. Use fetch or axios for API calls to leave-api service. Handle errors with user-friendly messages. Use basic styling with CSS or a UI library like Material-UI. Dockerfile: multi-stage build with Node 18, npm install, npm run build, serve with nginx:alpine copying build to /usr/share/nginx/html. Expose port 3000 via nginx config.\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"name\": \"leave-api\",\n            \"componentType\": \"service\",\n            \"language\": \"Go\",\n            \"dependsOn\": [],\n            \"entrypoint\": \"deployment/service\",\n            \"buildpack\": \"docker\",\n            \"appPath\": \"/leave-api\",\n            \"openAPISpec\": \"openapi: 3.0.3\\ninfo:\\n  title: Leave API\\n  version: 1.0.0\\n  description: Backend API for leave request management\\npaths:\\n  /health:\\n    get:\\n      summary: Health check\\n      responses:\\n        '200':\\n          description: OK\\n          content:\\n            application/json:\\n              schema:\\n                type: object\\n                properties:\\n                  status:\\n                    type: string\\n                    example: ok\\n  /requests:\\n    get:\\n      summary: List leave requests\\n      parameters:\\n        - name: employee\\n          in: query\\n          schema:\\n            type: string\\n          description: Filter by employee ID\\n        - name: manager\\n          in: query\\n          schema:\\n            type: string\\n          description: Filter by manager ID (shows team requests)\\n        - name: status\\n          in: query\\n          schema:\\n            type: string\\n            enum: [pending, approved, rejected]\\n          description: Filter by status\\n      responses:\\n        '200':\\n          description: List of leave requests\\n          content:\\n            application/json:\\n              schema:\\n                type: array\\n                items:\\n                  $ref: '#/components/schemas/LeaveRequest'\\n    post:\\n      summary: Submit a leave request\\n      requestBody:\\n        required: true\\n        content:\\n          application/json:\\n            schema:\\n              type: object\\n              required: [employeeId, startDate, endDate, leaveType]\\n              properties:\\n                employeeId:\\n                  type: string\\n                startDate:\\n                  type: string\\n                  format: date\\n                endDate:\\n                  type: string\\n                  format: date\\n                leaveType:\\n                  type: string\\n                  enum: [Annual, Sick, Casual]\\n      responses:\\n        '201':\\n          description: Request created\\n          content:\\n            application/json:\\n              schema:\\n                $ref: '#/components/schemas/LeaveRequest'\\n        '400':\\n          description: Invalid input\\n  /requests/{id}:\\n    patch:\\n      summary: Approve or reject a leave request\\n      parameters:\\n        - name: id\\n          in: path\\n          required: true\\n          schema:\\n            type: string\\n      requestBody:\\n        required: true\\n        content:\\n          application/json:\\n            schema:\\n              type: object\\n              required: [status, managerId]\\n              properties:\\n                status:\\n                  type: string\\n                  enum: [approved, rejected]\\n                managerId:\\n                  type: string\\n                comment:\\n                  type: string\\n      responses:\\n        '200':\\n          description: Request updated\\n          content:\\n            application/json:\\n              schema:\\n                $ref: '#/components/schemas/LeaveRequest'\\n        '404':\\n          description: Request not found\\n        '400':\\n          description: Invalid input\\n  /balance:\\n    get:\\n      summary: Get leave balance for a user\\n      parameters:\\n        - name: employeeId\\n          in: query\\n          required: true\\n          schema:\\n            type: string\\n      responses:\\n        '200':\\n          description: Leave balance by type\\n          content:\\n            application/json:\\n              schema:\\n                type: object\\n                properties:\\n                  employeeId:\\n                    type: string\\n                  balances:\\n                    type: object\\n                    additionalProperties:\\n                      type: number\\n                    example:\\n                      Annual: 15\\n                      Sick: 10\\n                      Casual: 5\\ncomponents:\\n  schemas:\\n    LeaveRequest:\\n      type: object\\n      properties:\\n        id:\\n          type: string\\n        employeeId:\\n          type: string\\n        managerId:\\n          type: string\\n        startDate:\\n          type: string\\n          format: date\\n        endDate:\\n          type: string\\n          format: date\\n        leaveType:\\n          type: string\\n          enum: [Annual, Sick, Casual]\\n        status:\\n          type: string\\n          enum: [pending, approved, rejected]\\n        comment:\\n          type: string\\n        createdAt:\\n          type: string\\n          format: date-time\\n        updatedAt:\\n          type: string\\n          format: date-time\",\n            \"componentAgentInstructions\": \"Build a Go HTTP service using net/http. Listen on port 9090. Implement GET /health returning JSON {\\\"status\\\":\\\"ok\\\"}. Use in-memory data structures (maps, slices) for storage: a slice of LeaveRequest structs and a map of employee balances. LeaveRequest struct: ID (string, UUID), EmployeeID (string), ManagerID (string), StartDate (time.Time), EndDate (time.Time), LeaveType (string: Annual/Sick/Casual), Status (string: pending/approved/rejected), Comment (string), CreatedAt (time.Time), UpdatedAt (time.Time). Initialize with sample data: 3 employees with IDs emp1, emp2, emp3; manager IDs mgr1, mgr2; balances map with Annual:15, Sick:10, Casual:5 per employee. Seed 2-3 pending requests. POST /requests: parse JSON body, validate required fields and date range (endDate >= startDate), generate UUID, set status=pending, store, return 201 with created object. GET /requests: support query params employee, manager, status; filter in-memory slice; manager filter returns requests where request.ManagerID equals query param; return filtered array. PATCH /requests/{id}: find by ID, validate status is approved or rejected, update Status, ManagerID, Comment, UpdatedAt; return 200 with updated object or 404 if not found. GET /balance?employeeId=X: return JSON object with employeeId and balances map. Use encoding/json for marshaling. Enable CORS headers (Access-Control-Allow-Origin: *, Access-Control-Allow-Methods: GET,POST,PATCH,OPTIONS, Access-Control-Allow-Headers: Content-Type). Handle OPTIONS preflight. Use http.HandleFunc for routing or a lightweight router like gorilla/mux. Log requests to stdout. Dockerfile: FROM golang:1.21-alpine AS builder, WORKDIR /app, COPY go.mod go.sum ./, RUN go mod download, COPY . ., RUN go build -o leave-api .; FROM alpine:latest, COPY --from=builder /app/leave-api /leave-api, EXPOSE 9090, CMD [\\\"/leave-api\\\"]. Ensure go.mod module name is leave-api. Use time.Parse for date parsing. Return appropriate HTTP status codes and error messages for validation failures.\"\n        }\n    ],\n    \"sourceSpec\": \"spec-v1\"\n}","stderr":"","interrupted":false,"isImage":false,"noOutputExpected":false}}
