{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01UwqUuGodb1UonA8hPeFJ3f","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01Ki6CUu81nyCxAtGQgZLfVR","name":"mcp__asdlc__submit_implementation","input":{"taskId":"92a12ff9-124a-4041-80e0-3cad6c0c7a01","summary":"Implemented the leave-api Go HTTP service with the following features:\n\n- GET /health → returns {\"status\":\"ok\"}\n- POST /requests → validates and creates a leave request (required fields, date range, leave type enum)\n- GET /requests → lists requests with optional filters: ?employee=, ?manager=, ?status=\n- PATCH /requests/{id} → approves or rejects a request with managerId and optional comment (404 if not found)\n- GET /balance?employeeId= → returns leave balances by type (Annual/Sick/Casual)\n\nImplementation details:\n- In-memory storage (slice + maps) with sync.RWMutex for thread safety\n- Seeded with 3 employees (emp1-3), 2 managers (mgr1-2), default balances (Annual:15, Sick:10, Casual:5), and 3 pending requests\n- Full CORS support (Access-Control-Allow-Origin: *, OPTIONS preflight handling)\n- UUID-based request IDs via github.com/google/uuid\n- Proper HTTP status codes: 200, 201, 400, 404\n- JSON error responses for all validation failures\n- Request logging to stdout via log package\n- Multi-stage Dockerfile (golang:1.21-alpine builder → alpine:latest runtime)\n- workload.yaml for OpenChoreo deployment on port 9090\n\nDocker image built and all endpoints verified locally.","port":9090,"filesCreated":["main.go","go.mod","go.sum","Dockerfile","workload.yaml","internal/models/leave.go","internal/store/store.go","internal/handlers/handlers.go"]},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":489,"cache_read_input_tokens":63724,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":489,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inf